quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  94,1,O Prophet! Have We not expanded your breast for you
  94,2,and relieved you from the burden
  94,3,which weighed down your back
  94,4,and exalted your fame
  94,5,Surely with every difficulty there is relief
  94,6,Surely with every difficulty there is relief
  94,7,"Therefore, when you are free from your daily task, devote your time to the labor of worship"
  94,8,and turn all your attention towards your Lord
  95,1,By the fig and by the olive
  95,2,by the mount of Sinai
  95,3,and by this city of peace (Mecca)
  95,4,We have indeed created man in the best stature
  95,5,then We abase him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,except those who believe and do good deeds - for they shall have a never ending reward
  95,7,"So, what causes them to disbelieve you concerning the Day of Judgment"
  95,8,Is not Allah the best of all judges
  96,1,Recite! (or read!) In the name of your Lord Who created
  96,2,created man from clots of blood
  96,3,Recite! Your Lord is the Most Gracious
  96,4,Who taught by the pen
  96,5,taught man what he knew not
  96,6,"Nay! Indeed, man transgresses all bounds"
  96,7,in thinking himself to be self-sufficient
  96,8,although surely towards your Lord is his return
  96,9,Have you seen the one (Abu Jahl) who forbids
  96,10,Our servant from offering Salah (prayer)
  96,11,"Have you considered, if He was on the right guidance"
  96,12,"or was enjoining true piety, why he would forbid someone from prayer"
  96,13,"Have you considered, if he denies the truth and turns away, what will happen"
  96,14,Does he not know that Allah is observing all things
  96,15,"Nay! Let him know that if he does not stop, We will drag him by the forelock"
  96,16,"a lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,So let him call his supporters for help
  96,18,We too shall call the guards of hell to deal with him
  96,19,Nay! Do not obey him! Prostrate yourself and bring yourself closer to your Lord
  97,1,Surely We have revealed this (Qur’an) in the night of Qadr
  97,2,"And what will make you understand, what the night of Qadr is"
  97,3,The night of Qadr is better than one thousand months
  97,4,"The angels and the Spirit (Gabriel) come down with every decree, by the leave of their Lord"
  97,5,"that night is the night of Peace, till the break of dawn"
  98,1,Those who are unbelievers from among the people of the Book and from the Pagans were not going to desist from their unbelief until the clear proof came to them
  98,2,"that is, a Messenger of Allah reciting to them holy scriptures from purified pages"
  98,3,containing infallible books
  98,4,Those who were given the Book before this (Qur’an) did not divide into sects until after there came to them a clear proof
  98,5,"Yet they were commanded nothing but to worship Allah, with their sincere devotion to Him, being True in their faith; to establish Salah ( prayers); and to pay Zakah (compulsory charity); and that is the infallible true Religion"
  98,6,"Surely those who disbelieve from among the people of the Book and the Pagans shall be in fire of hell, to dwell therein forever. They are the worst of all creatures"
  98,7,"Surely those who believe and do good deeds, are the best of all creatures"
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord shall be the gardens of Eden, beneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein forever. Allah shall be well pleased with them and they shall be well pleased with Him. That is for him who fears his Lord"
  99,1,When the earth will be shaken to her utmost convulsion
  99,2,and the earth shall bring out all her inner burdens
  99,3,"man shall say: \"What is happening to her"
  99,4,On that Day she shall report whatever had happened on her
  99,5,for your Lord shall have commanded her to do so
  99,6,On that Day men shall proceed in sorted out groups to be shown their ‘Book of Deeds.’
  99,7,"Then, whoever has done an atom’s weight of good shall see it there"
  99,8,and whoever has done an atom’s weight of evil shall see it there
  100,1,By the snorting war horses
  100,2,dashing off sparks by the strike of their hoofs
  100,3,making raids in the morning
  100,4,and leaving a trail of dust
  100,5,as they dash into the middle of the enemy troops
  100,6,Surely man is ungrateful to his Lord
  100,7,and surely he himself bears witness to it
  100,8,and surely he is violent in his love of this worldly wealth